== 2016 program == The 2016 Honda Celebration of Light took place on July 23, July 27, and July 30. The event featured the Netherlands, Australia, and the United States in competition. Notably, 2016 was the first time that the Netherlands has competed in the event.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vancitybuzz.com/2016/04/celebration-of-light-vancouver-2016-schedule-countries/|title=Honda Celebration of Light 2016 participating countries|author=Kenneth Chan|work=Vancity Buzz}}</ref> The Walt Disney Company, the world's largest consumer of fireworks,<ref name="Modern Marvels">{{cite AV media | people = Cindy Robinson; Jon Jefferson; Les Wooten | date = | year = 2006 | title = Modern Marvels - Walt Disney World (History Channel)| trans-title = | medium = DVD | url = | time = 44 minutes | location = New York| publisher = A&E Television Networks| id = |asin= B000CS461O| isbn = 9780767087896| oclc = 64282449| quote = | ref =}}<!--| access-date = April 11, 2016--></ref> was the competitor for the United States, while Australia was represented by Howard & Sons, whose displays have included the opening and closing ceremonies for [[2000 Summer Olympics]] in [[Sydney]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://vancouver.24hrs.ca/2016/04/07/vancouver-celebration-of-light-teams-unveiled|title=Vancouver|work=Vancouver 24 hrs}}</ref> and opening and closing ceremonies for the [[2010 Commonwealth Games]] in [[Delhi]] and [[2006 Commonwealth Games]] in [[Melbourne]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vancitybuzz.com/2016/04/honda-celebration-of-light-2016-fireworks-companies/|title=Opinion: Fireworks heavyweights push Honda Celebration of Light to new level|author=Kenneth Chan|work=Vancity Buzz}}</ref> Team USA won the competition.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Chan|first1=Kenneth|title=Disney wins 2016 Honda Celebration Of Light fireworks competition|url=http://dailyhive.com/vancouver/disney-wins-2016-honda-celebration-of-light-fireworks|publisher=Daily Hive|accessdate=August 1, 2016|date=August 1, 2016}}</ref> Vancouver Police had to shut down English Bay Beach for the Team USA show, due to capacity concerns.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Chan|first1=Kenneth|title=Police closed English Bay Beach due to record Celebration of Light crowds on Disney night|url=http://dailyhive.com/vancouver/vancouver-police-english-bay-closed-fireworks|publisher=Daily Hive|accessdate=August 1, 2016|date=July 31, 2016}}</ref>
